headline: Goldman’s Solomon Bullish on Dealmaking, but Expects ‘Speed Bump’
summary: Goldman Sachs's chief executive reiterated a bullish forecast for mergers and acquisitions in 2026, but cautioned about a possible speed bump ahead.  CEO David Solomon said Tuesday that the level of M&A activity would be meaningfully higher than it has been over the last five years.  "There isn't a CEO in the world that hasn't woken up and said, now is a moment for some period of years where I can do things strategically to strengthen my competitive position,” he said at the UBS Financial Services Conference.
